what is aipan
aipan is our traditional art made on floors and walls with red clay and rice paste
when is aipan made
it is made during every auspicious occasion like festivals and weddings
what do the designs in aipan signify
they are symbols of gods and are made for good fortune
what is a jaagar
jaagar is a ritual where we invoke our local deities by singing songs
who sings the songs in a jaagar
