it is a ritual where pulses are offered symbolizing a prayer for abundance
why should married daughters not be at their maternal home during harela
it is believed the daughter should be rooted in her own home like a sapling
what is the chhyo ceremony
it is a purification ceremony done on the eleventh day after a childs birth
what is the role of the maternal uncle in a wedding
the maternal uncle performs many important rituals like the dhuliarghya
why is a conch shell blown during puja
its sound is considered auspicious and drives away negative energy
are these festivals related to the seasons
what are nyole songs
they are songs of separation often sung by women remembering their maternal homes
why is the crow considered special on ghughutiya
crows are considered ancestors messengers and feeding them is like feeding our forefathers
do we have a festival like raksha bandhan
yes it is called chaitol and is celebrated for the welfare of the entire village
what is the meaning of de hara bharyun bhakar in the phool dei song
it is a wish for your granaries to always be full of green harvest
why is red color important in aipan
red color symbolizes auspiciousness and energy while white symbolizes purity
who is airadi the deity of animals
yes airadi is worshipped for the well being and protection of livestock
what is the tradition of jethon ka maas
it seems every month has a festival or custom in kumaon
that is the beauty of our culture it keeps us connected to our roots
what is basant panchami in our hills
on this day people wear yellow clothes and it marks the beginning of spring
why do we worship tools on harela
do we also celebrate diwali
yes but our diwali called budi diwali is sometimes celebrated a month later
is there a tradition of playing with colors like holi
yes we have baithki holi and khadi holi where we sing classical songs
what is chyur butter
it is a special butter from the chyura tree used in rituals and as medicine
why do some people fast during festivals
fasting is a way to purify the body and mind and show devotion
what is the janeu ceremony
it is the sacred thread ceremony for boys marking a new stage of life
why are folk tales important for our festivals
they teach the next generation the meaning and history behind our customs
do we have folk dances during festivals
yes like the chholiya dance which is a martial dance performed during weddings
what is the significance of the river in our festivals
rivers are considered sacred mothers many rituals are performed there
which deity is mainly worshipped in harela
mainly lord shiva harela is considered the wedding anniversary of shiva and parvati
why is bhaitauli more important for sisters
is it true that the ghughute garland must have an odd number of ghughutes
yes an odd number is considered auspicious in our traditions
who is the purohit and what is his role
the purohit is the family priest who conducts all religious ceremonies
what is bat pooja
it is the worship of the banyan tree by women for the long life of their husbands
why are festivals less grand now
people are busy and many have migrated the sense of community has reduced
what should we do to keep our customs alive
you young people must participate in them and understand their meaning
can i also learn to make aipan
of course it is our art everyone should learn it
what is the special prasad of golu devta
white cloth and white sweets are offered to golu devta
why is the harela festival celebrated three times a year
what is the dhol sagar
it is an ancient text containing all the knowledge and beats of playing the dhol drum
is the date of our festivals fixed
no they are based on the lunar calendar so the date changes every year
why is it important to visit the family deitys temple
to seek their blessings for the well being of the entire family line
will you teach me the songs of holi
yes with great pleasure you must learn them
