do you remember our old schools broken benches
yes i do we used to fight to get the one good one
we used to get beaten with a cane for not doing homework
my hands would swell up i could not even hold a roti
do you remember writing on a slate with chalk
yes and to erase it we would just use our saliva
during the lunch break i used to steal your tiffin
the biggest fear was when the teacher would say show me your nails
and if they were long you would get a ruler smack on the fingers
we used to run to ring the school bell before anyone else
and sometimes we would ring it ten minutes early for the final break
our school uniform was always torn
and the white shirt would turn yellow by the end of the day
i really enjoyed the morning assembly prayer
me too but after that the pt drill was very tiring
do you remember the annual function i had become a tree
yes and i was a monkey jumping around you
if you could not answer you would have to stand on the bench
we used to walk five kilometers to school yet we were never tired
because we used to eat wild berries along the way
the school bag felt heavier than our own weight
and on rainy days if the books got wet that was a separate beating
do you remember drawing mountains on the back of our notebooks
on sports day i always used to lose the race
but you were the champion of kabbadi no one could catch you
i used to drink water directly from the school tap
do you remember the murga punishment
my goodness yes my legs would tremble for hours after that
the biggest happiness was when a teacher was absent
that period would be a free period we would just make a racket
during the inspection we used to hide at the back
so that the officer would not ask us any difficult questions
we used to share one textbook among four boys
and when the turn came to read we would snatch the book
the school peon was stricter than the headmaster
he used to catch anyone trying to climb the wall
cleaning the classroom on saturdays was our duty
and we used to throw more dust on each other
what did you bring for lunch from home
usually roti with salt and chili or sometimes with jaggery
i was always chosen for the choir even with my bad voice
because you were tall and stood at the back just moving your lips
i found my old school report card i had failed in english
everyone used to fail in english our teacher himself did not know much
we used to make paper boats and float them in puddles
i still remember the multiplication tables we had to recite
up to twenty and if you fumbled the duster would come flying
mine too and filling ink into it was a big task
the girls section and boys section were separate
yes with a curtain in between but we still found ways to talk
the school library had only a few old torn books
and the librarian never let us issue them
the best part was the winter vacation
we used to finish the entire holiday homework on the last day
the moral science period was the only time we heard good stories
and the rest of the time we only got beaten
i got new shoes only once a year
and we had to make them last the whole year no matter how much they tore
there was a handpump in our school for water
and it took the effort of two boys to pump out a little water
yes but if they ever found out it would be a disaster
i always got the c grade in drawing class
you drew a mango that looked like a potato
the school walls were our canvas we would write our names with charcoal
and the next day the teacher would make us wipe it with our shirts
we used to play gilli danda during the lunch break
and many times the gilli would fly into the headmasters office
for the republic day parade we practiced for a whole month
those were some tough but beautiful days were not they
indeed brother the memories of that time are priceless
we had to fetch water from the river for the classroom floor
and we would splash half of it on each other on the way
remember the blackboard it was so cracked
yes whatever the teacher wrote half of it was illegible
my father used to check my school bag every evening
and my father used to ask me to recite the tables
the school had a small vegetable garden
and we had to water it as a punishment
i always came second in class you always came first
but you were the one who always helped me with my homework
we had to stand up and wish every time a teacher entered
and we had to do it about twenty times a day
i was very scared of the headmasters spectacles
he used to look over them like he knew all our mischief
the excitement of the last day of exams was unparalleled
we used to throw ink on each others shirts in celebration
remember how we made fun of the sanskrit teachers pronunciation
and one day he heard us and made us write aham gacchami a hundred times
our only source of general knowledge was the school notice board
and it was always a month old
i wish we could go back to those days just for one day
those carefree days will never come back my friend
is there any water in the spring today
no not a drop it has completely dried up this year
i had to walk all the way to the lower spring
it is the same story for everyone this summer is very harsh
did the government water supply come today
it came for just five minutes i could only fill one bucket
our old naula used to have water all year round
yes but now even that has dried up
how many buckets did you fill the line is so long
i have been standing here for an hour and have only filled two
my water pot slipped and broke on the way
the water is so muddy it is not fit for drinking
we have to filter it with a cloth what else can we do
i have told my son to bring a water tank from the city
that is a good idea at least it will last for a few days
carrying two buckets of water up this steep slope is so difficult
my shoulders are aching this has become our daily struggle
the cattle are thirsty there is not even enough water for them
we have to take them down to the river
my kitchen garden has completely dried up without water
forget the garden we barely have enough to drink
they have their own private line what about us poor folks
this year we must build a rainwater tank
yes if we save the rainwater it will be very helpful in the summer
child go and see if the water has come in the tap
grandma i have checked twice it is completely dry
do you remember when we used to bathe at the spring
now we have to think ten times even to wash our face
the water from the tanker tastes strange
it must be stored for many days boil it before drinking
my daughter in law is complaining
she says there is no water in this village
she is from the city she does not understand our struggles
i think we cut too many trees that is why the springs are drying up
you are absolutely right we did not care for nature now it is not caring for us
let us go we have to stand in line from 4 in the morning for water
this is not life half the day is spent just fetching water
the water in the earthen pot stays so cool
yes it is much better than the fridge water
they say a new water scheme is coming will we get water
we have been hearing this for ten years i will not believe it until i see it
the water level in the river has also gone down so much
there is no snow on the mountains so where will the water come from
my hands have become rough from washing clothes with less water
mine too there is no softness left in them
i am thinking of installing a handpump it will be expensive
the water problem is the biggest problem in our village
you are right without water there is nothing
i have stored two buckets of water just for cooking
good thinking we have to use every drop wisely
the children do not understand the value of water they waste it
they have not had to fetch it from miles away
i heard that in sharma jis house they had a fight over water
if it does not rain well this time i do not know what will happen
let us pray to the gods only they can save us now
the water from the spring is so sweet and digestive
that is true this tap water has no taste
half of my day is spent waiting for my turn at the spring
and the other half is spent worrying about the next days water
my grandfather used to say a village is known by its water
he was right our villages water was once famous
yes let us run otherwise we will not get even a single bucket
this plastic water tank gets so hot in the sun
and the water becomes undrinkable
we should all complain to the bdo about this
who listens to us poor people we have complained many times
the water pipe is broken up there and all the water is going to waste
and here we are longing for every single drop
i have started washing utensils with ash to save water
we are going back to the old ways out of compulsion
is there any government scheme for rainwater harvesting
there are schemes but they only exist on paper
this water scarcity is causing more quarrels in the village
when the stomach is thirsty anger comes quickly
that is very clever we must not waste anything
the spring near the temple still has a little water
that is the grace of the goddess that spring never dries up completely
my children in the city do not believe our water problems
they get water 24 hours a day just by opening a tap
the water feels so heavy to carry today
it is not the water sister it is our tiredness that feels heavy
they sell it there they are making a business out of our scarcity
how many trips do you make in a day to fetch water
at least four to five and still it is never enough
and i wish my daughter in law would not have to face this same struggle
the government should plant more trees that hold water
they plant them but who looks after them
the water is flowing slowly like a thread
it will take an hour to fill one pot
let us go it is getting dark and the path is not safe
yes let us hurry we have to cook dinner as well
i am using the same water to wash vegetables and then water the plants
that is the only way to manage in this scarcity
the water from our spring is so good for health
it is like nectar that is why people from far away come to take it
everyone is doing the same cleanliness has become a luxury
the water level in our rainwater tank is also getting low
we must use it very carefully now the rains are still far away
my son filled the buckets but he is complaining about his backache
it is not their daily job they are not used to this hardship
the water has a slight salty taste today
the source must be getting very low this is the last bit of water
i have kept all my big utensils out hoping for rain
me too even a little shower would be a great relief
they say in the olden days people used to worship the springs
they knew its value we have forgotten everything
this water problem makes me want to leave the village
but where is the peace of the village in the city we are stuck
the clothes are not getting cleaned properly with this hard water
and it consumes a lot of soap too
i saw a snake near the spring yesterday
be careful even animals are coming out in search of water
the government tap is broken and no one comes to fix it
this is the story of every village we have to manage on our own
i am giving water to my children as if it is milk
we have to they do not understand the scarcity
the water has become the most precious thing in our village
more precious than gold and silver
the water in the storage tank is finished what will we do tomorrow
we will have to go to the river there is no other option
i miss the sound of the flowing spring
now there is only the sound of empty buckets
the guests have arrived and there is no water to offer them
this is the biggest embarrassment
the village meeting is about the water problem today
my entire body aches from carrying water
this is the fate of us mountain women
the water is coming but the pressure is very low
at this rate my turn will come by the evening
i have started using disposable plates to save water
how long can we manage like this we need a permanent solution
the water from the distant spring is very cold even in summer
all the women gather at the spring it has become a meeting point
yes all the village gossip happens right there
the government should give us a subsidy for water tanks
they should give us water first then we will think about tanks
i am tired i have been walking for water since morning
sit down sister have some water first oh there is no water
this years drought is worse than ever before
it feels like a curse i do not know what sins we have committed
the price of water tankers has also doubled
they are taking advantage of our helplessness
you are lucky we have to stay here and face this
my eyes are tired of looking at the sky
brother did the mason come today
this wall has developed a huge crack it might fall
we need to repair it immediately it is not safe
did you bring the sand and lime from the market
i brought the lime the sand will arrive by evening on the mule
the monsoon is near we must get the roof laid quickly
he takes eight hundred rupees and the laborer takes five hundred
the old stone wall of the cowshed has collapsed
we will have to rebuild it with stone and mud
we have run out of cement the work has stopped
send someone to the road head immediately to bring more
which soil should we use for plastering the walls
bring the sticky black soil from the lower field
the foundation of the house needs to be deep and strong
yes all the strength of the house depends on its foundation
ram is building a two story house he must have spent a lot
yes building a house has become very expensive nowadays
this mason works very slowly it has been a month
slow work is fine but it should be good work
the roof is leaking right over my bed
put a bucket underneath for now we will fix it after the rain stops
carrying stones from the river is a very difficult task
the wooden beams for the roof have arrived
are they of good quality they must be strong
the walls are still damp we can not paint them yet
let them dry in the sun for a few more days
the mason is asking for an advance payment
the courtyard floor is uneven it needs to be leveled
we will level it with mud and then plaster it with cow dung
the window frame is loose it needs to be fixed
the carpenter will come tomorrow he will fix it
there is a good carpenter in the neighboring village
i had to take a loan from the bank to build this house
everyone has to building a house is no small feat
the water for mixing cement needs to be clean
yes otherwise the strength of the wall is reduced
this time let us make a bigger kitchen
yes the old one is too small
i saw shyams new house it has a modern design
but our old stone houses have a charm of their own
how many bags of cement will be needed for the roof
at least fifty to sixty bags will be required
the plaster on the outer wall is peeling off
it must not have been cured properly with water
the laborers are asking for tea all the time
we have to keep them happy otherwise they will not work properly
the work stopped today because of the rain
we need to leave space for the windows while building the wall
yes i have already told the mason the measurements
haris mason ran away with the advance money
that is why one should always hire a known and trusted person
we need to put a lintel over the door
yes it will support the weight of the wall above it
the cost of iron rods has increased a lot
everything has become expensive it is difficult to build a house
yes starting on a good day ensures the work goes smoothly
the verandah floor needs repairing
we can get it cemented this time
this time we will make a toilet inside the house
that is very important especially for the women and children
the old wooden staircase is creaking
we should replace it with a cement one
i am tired of all this construction noise and dust
it is a matter of a few more days then there will be peace
yes curing is very important for strength
the mason is experienced he knows all this
the neighbor is complaining about the sand and gravel on the path
how much will the painting cost
it depends on the quality of the paint it could be ten to fifteen thousand
the government is giving money for building houses
yes but getting it is a huge hassle due to paperwork
the main door should be large and beautiful
yes the main door is the first impression of the house
the stone from our own fields is the best
yes it is strong and costs nothing
yes a modern kitchen is incomplete without it
this masons work is very neat
he might be slow but his finishing is excellent
the wall is leaning to one side is this a problem
yes a big problem we must tear it down and rebuild it
we need to get the electrical wiring done before plastering
yes i have called the electrician he will come day after tomorrow
today we need to bring the wooden door frames from the market
okay let us go in the afternoon we will have to hire a vehicle
how long will it take for the whole house to be ready
if the work goes on continuously it should be done in three months
the floor of this room is still just mud
we will get it cemented after the roof is done
that is why people are using iron frames for doors and windows now
that old wall is covered in moss and looks very weak
yes it needs to be repaired the dampness is damaging it
the mason is very good but he drinks too much in the evening
the new wall needs to be plastered from both sides
yes it will make it stronger and protect it from the weather
where did you get these beautiful carved stones for the window
the water tank needs to be placed on the roof
we need to build a strong platform for it first
building a house drains all your lifes savings
true but having your own roof over your head is a great comfort
yes it is the best one available in the market
the mud plaster keeps the house cool in summer
and warm in winter our ancestors were very wise
okay i will talk to them today itself
the porch needs a railing for safety
we can get a simple iron railing made
his house was built so quickly
he had put a lot of masons and laborers on the job
we will get it repainted after the rains
this time let us make the windows bigger for more light
that is a good idea the rooms will feel more open
all the sand has been used up we need to bring more
this construction work consumes a lot of material
the kitchen slab should be made of stone
yes it is easy to clean and very durable
i am worried about the budget it keeps increasing
that always happens in construction we have to keep extra money aside
the new paint is smelling a lot
keep the windows open the smell will go away in a day or two
after the house is built we have to do the griha pravesh puja
yes only after that should one start living in the new house
the scaffolding for the roof is ready
good now the mason can start the work tomorrow
this wall is not straight at all
this mason seems to be an apprentice his work is not clean
let us put a small window in the storeroom for ventilation
yes otherwise it will get damp and musty
the cost of carrying one bag of cement up here is one hundred rupees
the transport costs more than the material itself
the old house needs a new coat of lime wash
it will start looking new again
the mason is saying he needs a helper
of course he cannot do all the heavy lifting alone
once the house is built there will be so much peace
but the loan installments will be a headache for years
a black cat just crossed our path
let someone else pass first it is a bad omen
my left eye has been twitching since morning
that is a good sign for women you might hear some good news
yes even my heart is feeling uneasy
do not call him from behind he is leaving for a journey
a crow is cawing on the roof
that is not a good sign the work might not be successful
do not sweep the floor after sunset
the temple flag is fluttering wildly but there is no wind
it is a sign from the deity something is about to happen
my right palm is itching i might get some money
if the left one itches then money goes away
the milk boiled over and spilled this is a bad omen
just offer a little bit to the fire god
a dog was howling outside our house all night
a dogs cry at night is not good it signifies sorrow
i sneezed just as he was leaving
you should have asked him to wait for a moment
it is a sign that a quarrel might happen in the house
i saw myself crying in my dream what does it mean
crying in a dream is actually good it means a problem will be solved
a vulture is sitting on haris roof this is very inauspicious
may golu devta protect his family
do not wash your hair on thursday
yes my mother used to say it is not good for the brothers
if you see a mongoose it is a very good omen
yes it is said that the work will definitely be successful
a piece of burning wood fell out of the hearth
it means a guest is coming
why is it forbidden to go near the peepal tree at noon
