i will miss sharing my tiffin with you
no one makes aloo gutke like your mother
i will eat it all by myself and remember you
when you come back bring some sweets from the city for me
i will bring a big box for you
so you are finally leaving our small river and going to a big city
do not cry so much your makeup will get ruined
i am leaving all of you
we will always be here for you
that is my only strength
are you nervous about going to a new home
everything will be new
you will win everyone's heart in no time
remember how we used to play gilli-danda with the boys
i was better than all of them
now you will have to play saas-bahu games
shut up do not scare me
this house will feel incomplete without you
now you are the man of the house
you just be happy in your new home
i cannot imagine this path to the spring without you
now you will have to go alone to fetch water
the path will feel so long and the pot so heavy
make new friends but do not replace me
so now you will wear beautiful sarees and jewelry every day
are you teasing me
do not change for anyone
do you remember how we got punished together by the teacher
he made us stand outside the class for the whole day
now you are going to a new school where your mother-in-law will be the teacher
it feels like just yesterday we were little girls playing with dolls
time flies so fast
i will keep your favorite doll safe
give it to my younger sister
your in-laws village is very far away
you must come for the village festival
things change friend that is life
now that you are leaving our little gang is broken
no it's not broken now you have one more home to visit in another village
that's true we will come to trouble you at your in laws place
you must come i will be waiting
you look so pretty in the bridal dress but your eyes are sad
i am happy but i am also sad to leave my home
it is the fate of every girl you will make your new house a home
i hope i can i am very nervous
our whole childhood is flashing before my eyes today
mine too from the first day of school to today
how quickly we grew up
i wish we could be children again just for one day
after you leave who will i share my secrets with
you can always tell me on the phone i will always be your best friend
it's not the same as talking face to face
i know but we have to make do with this now
remember how we used to dream about our weddings
yes we used to say we would get married in the same house
look at destiny you are going so far away
your mother in law seems very strict will you be able to manage
i will win her heart with my work and behavior
you are very brave i would be scared to death
life teaches you everything i will learn too
the bidai ceremony is so painful i can't watch it
