i wish this tradition didn't exist
i've brought water from our spring for you to drink one last time
thank you i will never forget its sweet taste
the city water has no life in it
i will miss this water the most
i am looking at you in your bridal dress and remembering our childhood games
it feels like i'm playing another game of bride bride
but this time it's for real
yes this time it's for real
when you have children will you tell them our stories
of course i will tell them all about our mischief and our friendship
i hope they also find a friend like you
and i hope they find a friend like you
i hope so my whole life is now with him
he will keep you happy we saw it in his eyes
your words give me strength thank you my friend
don't say last time i will come back and we will sit here again
but it won't be the same you will be someone else's
but i will always be your friend first
take care of yourself in the big city people are not like us there
i will brother and you take care of our fields and our home
i will manage everything you just live your life happily
goodbye my brother
here take this soil from our village with you
why friend what will i do with this
whenever you miss home just smell it you will feel we are all near you
you will make me cry this is the most precious gift
remember the old banyan tree at the edge of the village
yes we carved our names on it with a stone
