the beauty of a full moon night in the mountains is something else
it makes you forget all your worries
the water in the river is icy cold now
it's difficult to even put your hand in it
and we have to wash clothes in this water
our hands go numb the life of a mountain woman is not easy
i'm making pickles from the summer vegetables to eat in winter
that's a good idea in winter there are not many fresh vegetables
this is how we preserve the taste of one season for another
the sound of thunder makes my heart jump
me too i quickly go and light a lamp in the puja room
my grandmother used to say one should chant the name of god
it gives courage
the first spring flowers have bloomed
now the children will celebrate the phool dei festival
they will go door to door with flowers and rice
it's a beautiful tradition that welcomes the new season
the cobwebs in the house increase so much during the monsoon
and the walls get black with dampness
cleaning the house is a constant task in this season
the winter sun is good for making potato chips
yes they dry perfectly without getting burnt
and then we can fry and eat them all year
our village ways are the best
living in one room with the fire burning all day makes me feel suffocated
but what to do the cold outside is unbearable
i wish winter would end soon
patience friend every season passes
the cool breeze in autumn makes you want to just wander in the fields
yes with the sun on your back and a light coolness in the air
it's the most comfortable weather of the entire year
i completely agree with you
the season of khatarua is here we will burn the bonfire
and we will offer cucumbers to the fire
our festivals are so deeply connected to the seasons
it's so difficult to get up for morning chores in the biting cold
true the water feels like ice
and the hands refuse to work
but the work has to be done whether it's cold or hot
the sunlight is very good for getting vitamin d
yes especially the morning sun in winter
that's why our elders used to sit in the sun for hours
they knew the secrets to a healthy life
i'm planting marigolds for the autumn season
they will bloom beautifully around diwali
and we can use them for the puja
flowers make the festivals even more beautiful
there are puddles everywhere after the rain
and the children are splashing in them happily
let them childhood should be like this
yes carefree and full of joy
the elections for the pradhan are near again
yes now all the candidates will come to our doors with folded hands
and after winning they disappear for five years
that is the story every time brother
who are you going to vote for this time
i will vote for the one who promises to fix our village road
they all make promises no one does the work
still we have to trust someone
last night the candidate was distributing blankets and money
he is trying to buy votes don't fall for it
we will take the blanket but vote for the deserving one
our vote is not for sale
the current pradhan has not done any work at all
he just filled his own pockets the school wall is still broken
this time we must not let him win
the whole village is angry with him
two brothers are standing against each other in the election
this politics will ruin their family relationship
this greed for power is a bad thing
it makes brothers into enemies
the candidate's speech was very fiery today
he was saying he will bring a hospital to the village
we have been hearing this promise for twenty years
yes everyone dresses up and goes to vote
it's our duty after all
they are dividing the village on the basis of caste for votes
this is very wrong a pradhan is for the entire village
the son of the current pradhan is very arrogant
he roams around as if he is the prince of the village
the father's power has gone to his head
this time the villagers will teach them a lesson
i don't understand this politics they are all the same
but it is important to vote otherwise the wrong person will win
alright i will go who do you think is a good candidate
i think the school teacher is a good man he is educated and honest
the government has reserved the pradhan's seat for a woman this time
that's very good women should also get a chance
but their husbands will run the show from behind
even so it's a start things will change slowly
there was a big fight between the supporters of two candidates yesterday
this always happens during elections it spoils the village atmosphere
they were abusing each other badly
this enmity will last for years now
which symbol has your candidate got
he has got the rising sun symbol
and ours has got the hand pump
let's see whose sun rises and whose pump gives water
the candidate came to our house and touched my feet
they become very humble before the elections
and after winning they don't even recognize you
this is the nature of politics
i'm tired of these election rallies and the noise
their vehicles have ruined our narrow village paths
they only care about their votes not our troubles
grandma i'm feeling very weak and feverish
i drank it but i'm not feeling any better
then let's go to the dispensary tomorrow we must show it to the doctor
my father's knee pain has increased a lot in this cold
massage it with warm mustard oil it will provide relief
we do that every day but the pain is old
old ailments trouble a lot during winter
and if he is he just gives the same red and yellow pills for every illness
it's better to go to the private doctor in the market
but he charges a very high fee
the child has a stomach ache what home remedy should i try
give him a little ajwain with warm water he will get relief
he must have eaten something wrong
children are like that they put anything in their mouths
this seasonal cough and cold is troubling everyone
yes every household has someone who is sick
this changing weather is very bad for health
true one has to be very careful
my grandfather doesn't want to take the english medicines
old people trust more in herbs and home remedies
to some extent he is right but for serious illnesses they are necessary
my mother's blood pressure is high again
did she stop taking her medicine
yes she said she was feeling fine so she stopped
this medicine has to be taken for life you must explain this to her
there's no good hospital in our area we have to go to the city for every little thing
and that costs so much money and trouble
if someone falls seriously ill at night there's no hope
this is the biggest problem of living in the mountains
apply turmeric powder immediately it will stop the bleeding and prevent infection
i have done that is it enough
if the cut is deep you should still show it to the compounder
the health workers came to the village today
what did they say did they give any medicines
they were giving vaccinations to the children
that's good it protects them from many diseases
ever since i've come back from the city i've had an upset stomach
it's the change of water drink water from the village spring you'll be fine
the water here is so light and digestive
it's like nectar the city water is just chemicals
look at that house it's been locked for so many years
yes everyone in that family has moved to the city
our village is slowly turning into a bhoot gaon ghost village
ram's son also left for delhi yesterday
one by one all the young men are leaving
who will look after the fields and the elderly
this is a very worrying situation
i miss the days when the village was full of people and laughter
now there's just silence and empty houses
what can be done there are no jobs here
the walls of the old abandoned house are collapsing
without people even houses die
it used to be such a beautiful house
now only memories remain
when my children come for holidays the house feels alive again
but as soon as they leave the same silence returns
i wish they would stay here forever
but their future is in the city we have to accept that
yes all the young have migrated
who will carry our bier when we die
don't say such things god will take care of everything
the fields are becoming barren because there's no one to cultivate them
and the wild animals have ruined the rest
it's a very painful sight
i hear strange noises from the empty house at night
it must be the wind or some animal
or maybe ghosts who knows
don't scare me now i won't be able to sleep
our village used to have so many festivals and fairs
now there are not enough people to even celebrate properly
this is the biggest loss of migration
i feel like a guest in my own village when i come back
why do you say that this is your home
because so many new faces are here and all my old friends have left
the village is not the same as you left it
that candidate is making tall promises again about building a road
he had said the same thing five years ago did he do anything
nothing at all he just filled his own house with wealth
this time he won't get a single vote from my family
the child has had a cough for many days the syrup from the dispensary is not working
okay i will try that today these new medicines are useless
look at the beautiful carving on the door of this empty house
it's sad that there is no one to even light a lamp here
the house is waiting for its people to return
the whole village is divided into two factions because of this election
brothers are not talking to brothers
this politics is a very dirty game
after the election everything will be forgotten but the bitterness in relationships will remain
i had to take my mother to the city hospital it was so much trouble
is she alright what did the doctor say
health is the biggest problem in these remote areas
my grandson came from delhi he can't even speak two words of kumaoni
this is the problem with children born in the city
he feels like a stranger in his own village
if we leave our roots this is what will happen
the candidate's posters are plastered on every wall it looks so ugly
they have dirtied the entire village
no one will clean them after the election is over
they just come to make things dirty and then leave
my body aches all the time i don't know what's wrong
it must be weakness you work too hard and don't eat enough
what to do there is so much work in the house and fields
but health comes first take care of yourself
if everyone leaves the village who will preserve our culture
that is a very big question i think about it every day
our festivals our language everything will be lost
it feels very frightening to think about it
this new young candidate seems educated and sensible
but does he have experience the old one knows everyone in the village
experience in doing what nothing but corruption
you've got a point maybe we should give the young man a chance
my son sent money from the city he sent it directly to the bank account
yes but i miss his letters that used to come with the money
that's true those letters had a different kind of warmth
there's a health camp in the village tomorrow
will doctors from the city come
yes they will check blood pressure and sugar for free
then we must all go such opportunities are rare
he must be embarrassed he was boasting so much
pride always comes before a fall
he got a good lesson
there are so many empty houses that the village feels haunted at night
and the barking of dogs echoes even more
sometimes i get scared in my own home
this loneliness is eating away at our villages
my joints ache more during the rainy season
yes the dampness increases the pain
keep your body warm and avoid sour things
no it requires a lot of money and government support
then what's the point of this election
just to handle the small disputes and works of the village
there used to be so much activity in the village during festivals
now there are not enough young people to even perform the jhoda dance
all our traditions are disappearing with the people
eating fresh greens from the fields keeps one healthy
that's true we don't need medicines as much
city people eat stale vegetables and then fall sick
our village food is the best medicine
the loneliness of old age is very difficult especially when children are far away
at least we have each other for support in the village
yes this neighborhood bond is our biggest strength
otherwise this loneliness would eat us alive
after winning the new pradhan threw a big feast for the village
this is just a show let's see if he actually works for five years
i have no hope they are all cut from the same cloth
you are absolutely right
i am happy
i am sad
i am tired
i am scared
i love you
i miss you
you are beautiful
you are my everything
i miss you a lot
you complete me
you are my best friend
our friendship is forever
i feel lucky to have you as a friend
friends like you are rare
you make my life brighter
happy birthday!
may you have a long and happy life
may all your dreams come true
wishing you health, wealth, and prosperity
happy new year!
may this year be full of happiness and success
may your life be filled with light and prosperity
happy holi!
may your life be as colorful as holi
give me water.
the water is cold.
i am drinking water.
bring a glass of water.
the river water is clean.
it is raining.
the water is very deep here.
i need hot water to bathe.
the water in the pitcher is finished.
don't waste water.
the water is flowing slowly.
my throat is drying up, I need water.
the fields need water.
this water is for drinking.
pour some more water.
the child is playing in the water.
keep the water covered.
how much water should I put in the tea?
the water is boiling.
